1.2.7	Shut down the comupters.	St
1.2.8	Unplug the power from the cable modem (clicking the power switch,if there is one won't do the job).	St
1.2.9	Plug the ethernet cable, which should be supplied, into the cable modem and the router WAN socket.	St
1.2.10	Install the software that comes with the router.	St
1.2.11	Windows XP SP2 and the latest version of Mac OS really shouldn't need any software, added, however.	St
1.2.12	Plug the ethernet cable from your desktop into one of the ports on the back of the router.	St
1.2.13	Plug the cable modem back in and wait for the lights to stabilize, which shows it is online and working.	St
1.2.14	Now, plug the power into the router and wait until the lights on it stop flashing (except for the ones which show activity.	St
1.2.15	The LED layout is in the manual) Boot the desktop.	St
1.2.16	It should see the internet once it is up and running.	St
1.2.17	Getting Wireless is a wee bit more complicated but no big deal.	St
1.2.18	Depending on which router you buy you will have different I.P.	St
1.2.19	addresses which you will use to talk to the router.	St
1.2.20	Open a browser and type in the I.P.	St
1.2.21	- like 192.168.1.1.	St
1.2.22	The last two will change by mfger.	St
